summary: An ordinance accepting a deed from W.W. Shields, as Treasurer of King County, State of Washington, to the City of Seattle, executed on the 19th day of August, 1924, and laying off West Holly Street, West Frontenac Street, West Myrtle Street, and alley between West Holly Street and West Frontenac Street, from a point 150 feet east of California Avenue to California Avenue.
